[ 1. Overview ]────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────//───

A premium bone-in cut, meticulously prepared and roasted. The rib bones have been
"frenched"—trimmed cleanly down to the main eye of the muscle—creating a stunning,
architectural presentation on the plate.

The cook achieved a beautiful Maillard reaction across the exterior, yielding a
deeply caramelized fat cap and a glistening, flavorful crust.

![Frenched Pork Rib Roast](/assets/smoked-pork-roast.jpg)

[ 2. Preparation Details ]─────────────────────────────────────────────────//───

### 1. The Frenched Rib Bones
*   #[G|Clean Presentation]: Excess fat and intercostal meat removed from the bone tips.
*   #[G|Heat Caramelization]: Roasted until the exposed bones developed a rich, dark brown char.

### 2. Herb & Spice Seasoning
*   #[G|Aromatic Crust]: Coated in a robust blend of dried green herbs (including rosemary and thyme)
    blended with garlic, coarse salt, and cracked black pepper.
*   #[G|Glistening Surface]: Rested and basted with its own rendered fat and light glaze to keep
    the meat succulent and moist.

[ 3. Technical Notes ]──────────────────────────────────────────────────────//───

Pork rib roasts require precise heat management. Cooking bone-in preserves moisture and
imparts deep, savory undertones to the surrounding meat. This roast was pulled at the
exact target internal temperature to ensure the meat remained juicy, tender, and fully
cooked without drying out.

Presented here resting on a classic crimson geometric rimmed plate on granite, ready for
carving.

